-- VTB Group to Increase Profit in 2011 to $2.6 Billion, Chairman Kostin Says
-- B y   E m m a   O ’ B r i e n
-- 2010-12-28T12:17:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-28/vtb-group-to-increase-profit-in-2011-to-2-6-billion-chairman-kostin-says.html
VTB Group, Russia’s second-largest
bank, plans to boost profit by 60 percent to 80 billion rubles
($2.6 billion) next year and to more-than double earnings in
2013 to as much as 140 billion rubles, Chairman Andrei Kostin
said at an event for the company in Moscow today.  The Moscow-based bank is targeting a share price of more
than 15 kopeks in 2013, Kostin added. VTB stock rose 0.1 percent
to 10.15 kopeks on the Micex index by 3:16 p.m. today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emma O’Brien at 
 eobrien6@bloomberg.net  